text.description1: A huge rock dive site in between Ajoi and Nayak, It’s a nice place for photographers and you don’t have to swim further out, an easy and shallow dive site, only 4 mins away from Juara Jetty.
text.description2: Full of nudibranch, flatworms, seaslug, even hairyshrimp, mix with corals and rocks, good to find small things.

text.description1: One hour far from Soul Scuba divers, usually the second dive on the Batanta trip, after the P-47 Wreck and before going in the jungle to discover the two waterfalls. This place is full of wobbegong.
text.description2: Wobbegong sharks, nudibranch, snapper, triggerfish, trevally, jackfish, clownfish, angelfish, butterflyfish.

text.description1: Algae Patch is a “muck“ dive site used by many liveaboards to/from Raja Ampat / Sorong. It’s in a channel, so you’ll need to watch the tide charts to avoid strong currents. Lots of sandy areas with coral blocks and teeming macro life.
text.description2: Nudys, Rhinopias, Scropion Leaffishes, Mimik-Octopus and Wonderpus have been seen here on regular base

text.description1: 45 minutes boat ride from Soul scuba divers, Airplane wreck lies between 26m-33 metre. Airplane wreck is from WW2 pacific war and its an American P-47D aircraft
text.description2: Airplane wreck, leaf scorpionfish, scorpion fish, flatheads, wrasse, damsel fish, groupers, snappers,

text.description1: Start against the current looking for schools of fishes then drift along the slope that alternatively change to walls. As you drift along, the coral becomes denser until reaching a nice coral garden. Don’t forget to look in the blue and look for schools of bumphead parrotfishes.
text.description2: White tip and black tip reef sharks, hawksbill turtles, school of bumphead parrotfishes, nudibranches, good for macro.

text.description1: Ten minutes boat ride away from Soul scuba divers, slopy wall, drift dive within many sharks and schools of fishes. The reef starts from 5 meter until 40 meters.
text.description2: White tip shark, black tip shark, eagle ray, snappers, sweetlips, spadefish, eels, fusiliers, surgeon fishes,

properties.name: Tapor Tamiyam, Cape Kri, Raja Ampat

text.description1: Cape Kri dive site is located on the northeastern end of Kri Island. A famous Raja Ampat dive site that holds the world record for the dive site with the highest number of species (374!) sighted on a single dive (record held by Gerald R. Allen, marine biologist)
text.description2: Amongst others you can see: schools of fusiliers, yellowtail barracuda, white tip sharks, black tip sharks, napoleon wrasse, red tooth triggerfish and beautiful corals.

text.description1: 15 minutes from closest dive center, busy dive spot with fish and sharks, mild to medium current, decent into the blue and drifting to the dive spot.
text.description2: Fusiliers, white tip shark, black tip shark, barracuda, tuna, triggerfish, wobbegong shark, angelfishes.

text.description1: Large seamount with depth from 3-30m. Amazing coral coverage and very rich for marine life as well. Often strong current which brings a lot of fish and action.
text.description2: Many different species of fish, sharks, garden eels, beautiful coral gardens, occasionally Manta rays passing.

text.description1: Ten minutes boat ride from Soul scuba divers dive centre, near to Cape kri dive site, amazing wall with lots of activity within sharks and fish schools. Take your torch because on the wall you have some nice overhangs and caves.
text.description2: Snappers, groupers, white tip reef shark, black tip reef sharks, barracuda, fusiliers, spanish mackrell, green turtles

text.description1: Ten minutes away from the Soul scuba divers dive centre, beautiful slope coral reef, drift dive site with plenty of action with fish and sharks.
text.description2: white tip shark, black tip shark, eagle ray, spade fish, fussiliers, tuna, groupers, pygmy seahorse, eels,

text.description1: Another shallow reef dive, however even with its similar topography to other sites, it delivers a vastly different set of species. Ever-present is large numbers of fusiliers and other colourful fish inhabiting the coral. It is known for its strong currents.
text.description2: Keep a look out for pipefish, pigmy seahorses, nudibranches, flatworms and some very interesting crabs and shrimps.

text.description1: Wonderful close by house reef right in front of Turtle Divers Raja Ampat center, offers sensation of slope colorful soft and hard corals combination. Average shallow between 12 - 16 meters with mostly light current condition give you calm and easy dive experience.
text.description2: Group of fusiliers, sweet lips, black tip playing along the reef, and napoleon wrasse often spotted here. puffer fish a well easy to find, big fish species normally only in the shalow

text.description1: 5 minutes boat ride away from the closest diving center, get drop to the wall and swim your way to the corner of fishy madness. Mild to medium current, beginners to advance levels.
text.description2: barracuda, fusiliers, surgeon fish, triggerfish, jacks, giant travelly, black tip sharks, jacks, green turtles, batfishes.

TURTLE DIVERS RAJA AMPAT, 98427 Yenbuba - South West Papua
TURTLE DIVERS RAJA AMPAT, 98427 Yenbuba - South West Papua

text.description1: Challenging dive site, This is the one site where anything can happen….and it usually does! Be ready for an amazing dive here! one of the most popular dive site in Raja Ampat
text.description2: Fantastic dive site for Grey reef sharks and when in season oceanic mantas, swarms of Spanish Mackerel, Giant Trevally, Barracuda, Dogtooth Tuna, Rainbow Runners, and countless Jacks

text.description1: Ten minutes boat ride from Soul scuba divers dive centre, epic wall dive site, best in high tides, many type of sharks and schools of fishies, near to Cape kri
text.description2: trigger fish, napoleon, parrotfish, white tip reef shark, black tip reef shark, fusiliers, groupers

text.description1: 15 minutes away from Soul Scuba divers dive centre, coral bummies, reef starts at 5 meters until 40 meters, fishy dive sites with lots of different schools of fishes. You can finish the dive on the top where the corals are amazingly colorfoul.
text.description2: Garden eels, black tip shark, white tip shark, tuna, barracuda, spanish mackrell, angelfish, butterfly fish, triggerfish

text.description1: Located in front of Warahnus Dive Homestay jetty, offers you variation big corals structures along the reef. Group of fusiliers playing on shallow 12 -15 meters, with variation of soft coral through the slope topography. Good for corals id program and wide angle photograph sites.
text.description2: Group of fusiliers, black tip sharks use to passing by the reef, sometimes you can show group of bum head too, napoleon wrasse, turtles, also if you can try to spot some leaf fish.

text.description1: Only 5 minutes far from Soul Scuba divers. This is drift dive during the day, that can bring you toward Cape Kri or bring you up to Soul Scuba’s jetty. Look at the nice coral but also in the blue, where sharks can pass by. This is also a favorite place for night dive!
text.description2: Black tip sharks, turtles, pufferfishes, school of fishes, macro at night, lobsters, shrimps and crabs.

text.description1: 5 minutes away from the closest dive center, easy slope with artificial and coral reef, entering water near to the jetty, mild current, easy for beginners.
text.description2: Spade fish, black tip shark, white tip shark, green turtle, hawkbill turtle, angelfish, snapper, grouper.

text.description1: 5 minutes away from the closest dive center, coral garden with slope, schools of fishes, good for pygmy seahorse and wobbegong sharks, mild current, easy for beginners
text.description2: Snappers, tuna, trevally, white tip reef shark, black tip reef shark, green turtle, hawkbill turtle, surgeon fish.

text.description1: North site of kri island near Soulscuba house reef. Don’t forget to have a look into the blue you can have some ocean gift manta ray passing by. And also some sharks.
text.description2: Beautiful reef where you can encounter turtles, napoleon wrasse, family of bumphead parrotfish, big school of fusilier, nudibranch, octopus, cuttlefish …

text.description1: In front of the Soul scuba divers dive shop, you can find epic sloping coral garden with lots of different species to discover. It can be done as a shore entry or with boat. Perfect for day or night dives.
text.description2: Spadefish, lionfish, coral garden, octopus, triggerfish, green turtle, hawkbill turtle, black tip shark, white tip shark, travelly.

text.description1: Only 5 minutes far from Soul Scuba divers, this site is perfect for the pool exercises for Open Water courses. This is also a favorite place for macro lovers on night dive! Sandy area with long algae, a fisherman net covering corals and lots of places for critters to hide. The maximum depth is around 10 m.
text.description2: Walking shark (Raja Epaulette shark), nudibranches, diamond file fishes, crabs, shrimps, ribbon eels, juvenile sweetlips, macro

text.description1: Great place for night dive and macro lovers. Only 5 minutes far from Waisai harbour and 30 minutes away of Soul Scuba divers with a speedboat. At dusk, the mandarine fishes can be seen and as the night come, explore the sand and the bummies where all the critters are hidden.
text.description2: Mandarinefishes, spidercrabs, orang-utan crabs, shrimps, nudibranches, wobbegong, scorpionfishes, etc.

text.description1: Be ready for adventure! This dive site is reserved for expert divers. The reef is only at 10-12 m deep but the current is very strong so you better have a hook! But if there is current, there are fishes.
text.description2: School of fishes, black and white tip reef sharks, nudibranches (if you have the time to see them), redtooth triggerfishes

text.description1: 5 minutes far from Soul Scuba divers, a nice coral slope for a drift dive. If the current is strong enough you might even drift until Soul Scuba divers jetty!
text.description2: Black tip sharks, rays, cuttlefishes, tutles, pufferfishes and many school of fishes. The reef is nice but don’t forget to look in the blue!

text.description1: 20 minutes away from closest dive center, deep dive site, good for advanced divers, medium to strong current, interesting coral formations with schools of fishes, possibility to finish the dive on the Mioskun dive site.
text.description2: Snappers, triggerfish, angelfish, reef sharks, sea turtles, sea snakes, eagle rays passing by, fusiliers.

text.description1: Starting this relaxing dive should be done on the current side of the island, leaving a good distance between the entry point and the best point of dive site on the south-eastern side
text.description2: Wobbegong shark sighting are common. Make sure to peer under the coral ledges for these strange creatures, while also looking for tiny Pontohi Pygmy sea horses.

text.description1: 10 minutes boat ride away from Soul scuba dive center, nice and easy dive site, suitable for beginner level divers, goof for underwater photogrpayhy
text.description2: Underwater coral reef, multiple different spices of fish, fussieliers, barracuda, black tip reef shark

text.description1: This is one of the main jetties to visit in the Raja Ampat area. You will spend a long time around the jetty. Once you swim away from the jetty, you will be surrounded by schools of fusiliers and amazing reefs.
text.description2: You will find 3 giant clams under the jetty. You will also encounter extremely large green turtles, as well as fantastic macro life.

text.description1: This is the new coral plantation location of the NGO the Sea People (Orang Laut). The goal is to plant 1 hectare of corals. Ask information at Soul Scuba divers to come, help and learn a lot about corals!
text.description2: Coral plantation, conservation project, macro in the sand and rubbles, nudibranchs, pipefishes, cuttlefish, pufferfish

text.description1: 15 minutes from Soul Scuba divers dive centre, you will arrive into a small little mushroom shaped island, where you will decent into shallow coral garden. Overhang and wall, you might want to take your Underwaterlight with you!
text.description2: Bumphead parrotfish, hawksbill turtle, green turtle, black tip reefshark, white tip reefshark, barracuda, tuna, trevally and pygmy seahorses.

text.description1: Head down the jetty at the Scuba Republic Raja Ampat Resort and with a giant stride straight into the water where you will find calm conditions and a beautiful house reef.
text.description2: Fringing coral reef including many different coral and fish species as well an abundance of macro life.

text.description1: Shallow reef with combination of soft and hard corals. Usually very mild current. If current gets stronger, possible to do drift dive as reef is long enough. The best depth to 3-14m
text.description2: Black tip reef sharks, cuttlefish, Crocodile fish, soft and hard corals, many small reef fish, beautiful coral garden,

text.description1: Colorful wall covered by soft corals, black corals and gorgonians. Depth 2-26m. Usually easy dive with time to search for macro. When current gets strong, great place for drift dive.
text.description2: Black corals, soft corals, Gorgonians, Pygmy seahorses, Wobbegong, Stingrays on the bottom, Mantis peacock shrimps, Nudibranch, snappers, batfish, fusiliers, trevallies, reef sharks

text.description1: Start in the sandy and rocky area where you can see nice macro and have some bigger animal passing by in the blue. Then you finish at the tip where the current is strong and bring a lot of fishes. The top coral garden is amazing and you can sometimes see mantas or schools of mobulas passing by.
text.description2: Black tip shark, manta, mobulas, school of fishes, nudibranchs, cuttlefishes, jacks, snappers, pufferfishes

text.description1: 45 minutes boat ride away from Soul scuba divers dive centre, remember look into blue for big sea creatures passing by, reef starts at 5 meter to 40 meter
text.description2: eagle rays, reef sharks, green turtle, hawkbill turtle, snappers, triggerfish, fusiliers, coral garden

text.description1: This site is named after a house guest at Biodiversity Resort who explored this area. Descending onto a shallow rock, your dive starts immediately with the welcoming site of colorful Anthias and Fusiliers.
text.description2: Blue spotted stingrays and the elusive pygmy seahorse are found here. In the shallows, poke your head under the overhangs to spot wobbegong sharks.

text.description1: This dive site is unique in that it is one of the very few wall dives that the Dampier Straight has to offer. The start of the wall has two small caves where you can spot fish swimming upside down, a strange thing to see for the first time.
text.description2: The wall is covered with gorgonian fan corals, sponges and whip tail corals right from the bottom of the wall to the surface. It is the perfect wall.

text.description1: Head straight out from Saporkren village with shore access straight into the water where you will find calm conditions and a beautiful fringing reef.
text.description2: Fringing coral reef including many different coral and fish species as well an abundance of macro life.

text.description1: With its Indonesian name meaning “Five Rocks,” this is a perennial favorite, with many of our guests requesting one or more returns to this site. Descending on the north-eastern side takes you down to the maximum depth of around 24m
text.description2: Large schools of Barracudas and the odd sitting of Mantas when in season. You can find the electric clam on this site in a few places

text.description1: The reef in front of Biodiversity Jetty and continous all the way to Batu Lima starts at 2m dropping down to 20m. The reef has many hidden areas for species to hide
text.description2: Under the jetty you it’s extremely common to discover the walking shark and Blacktip reef sharks swimming along the reef

text.description1: On the most favorable days, the current is strong. Try to start close to the drop off otherwise you better have freediving fins to move quicker and save deco time. On the drop off there is a great overhang from 28 to 35 m, you can then go deeper than 50 m. The end is on nice soft coral garden up to 5 m.
text.description2: On this underwater reef, be ready to see swimming fishes, marine corals, shell-less nudibranches. An occasional sub-aquatic manta might pass by.

text.description1: Kabui is a delightful secluded beach with a sandy bottom and reef patches scattered about. It provides calm and current free training conditions for courses or refreshers, or a gentle dive around its hard and soft coral bombies. You can sometimes get the chance of spotting Turtles and blue spotted rays.
text.description2: wonderful coral reef, with hidding nudibranches and spanish dancers at night can be seen here. schools of yellow snappers

text.description1: Lean or hook on the nice and flat sandy area at 16 m from where you can enjoy the show of the mantas getting cleaned. This is an easy manta dive site for beginners. While waiting for the manta to come, look for macro in the sandy area, you might even see a flamboyant cuttlefish!
text.description2: Reef and Manta, cleaner wrasses and angelfishes cleaning the mantas, remora , flamboyant cuttlefishes.

text.description1: 20 min boat ride from Soul scuba divers dive centre, Manta cleaning station, from dec-may you have chance to see reef and oceanic manta rays in this dive site. In 2022 the reef mantas were already here since end of August.
text.description2: reef manta rays, oceanic manta rays, eagle rays, mobula, black tip shark, white tip shark, grey reef shark

text.description1: Another beautiful reef discovered by us, on one of our exploratory trips. Sitting just inside the entrance of what is known as the lake between Waigo and Gam Islands.
text.description2: With dense hard corals in the shallows and a gentle slope it provides a chance to see frogfish and several different pipefish species and a wide verity of macro life.

text.description1: This is a challenging dive and not for the faint hearted. This jetty is a photographers dream with thousands of fish found under the jetty, such as schooling jacks hunting on the smaller silversides. It is not an easy dive due to the strong currents you can experience here.
text.description2: Soft and hard corals and giant clams, found to the one side of the jetty with lots of coral and pinnacles on the east side of the island.

text.description1: One hour away from Soul scuba divers dive centre. This is a narrow canyon, situated between Gam Island and Waigeo Island, good for macro lovers. The current might be strong and you can feel like flying in a river.
text.description2: Pygmy seahorse, flatworms, nudibranchs, sweetlips, stingrays, eels, turtles, sharks, angelfish, groupers.

text.description1: One hour boat ride from closest dive center, witness on the way the beautiful fauna that Raja Ampat has to offer. Macro to big schools of fishes. The endemic yellow coral that you find on this dive site gave the name of “Citrus“.
text.description2: Wobbegong sharks, eels, nudibranches, barracudas, fusiliers, breams, surgeonfish, triggerfish, octopus.

text.description1: One hour boat ride from Soul scuba divers dive centre, on the way to the dive site you can witness dolphins, pilot whales and many birds. The coral reef starts at 5-7 meters and continue until 40 meters.
text.description2: Wobbegong shark, white tip shark, black tip sharks, barramundi, jacks, barracuda, fusiliers, angelfish, butterfly fish,

text.description1: This dive site has one of the steepest slops and in some areas a wall dive. The main attraction for this dive site is the gorgonian coral that can be found here.This dive has many secrets, you just need to spend the time observing the reef while drifting by. It is a fantastic drift dive.
text.description2: You will be swept along with the current searching for macro life, like the Frogsfish and the many Nudi Branches of different species.csoft coral life is wonderful as you drift along t

text.description1: One of the more stunning dives sites in raja ampat. The color of the coral garden will blow your mind. Near piaynemo island you will enjoy the marvelous view point.
text.description2: Stuning nursery for fishes, huge biodiversity of coral. You may encounter some shark,tuna,napoleon wrasse, and a variety of macro life.

text.description1: 1 hour boat ride from Soul scuba divers dive centre, day trip with Piaynemo sightseings, wall dive covered with seafans and soft corals. Good for macro.
text.description2: Pygmy seahorse, black tip shark, spade fish, angelfish, hawkfish, midnight snappers, barracuda, angelfish, soldier fish,

text.description1: Located near to the famous Piaynemo, this dive sites is included in our day trips and it is around 1h30 hours away from Soul scuba divers dive centre. Boat dive, starting from the bay, wall, swim through in 5 meters, ending in a wonderful coral garden.
text.description2: Makerels, fusiliers, napoleon wrasse, humphead parrotfish, sea fans, bluefin travelly, triggerfish, pufferfish...
